morphospeciesIDRemarks: Stem glabrous green 4-angled and grooved; branching from leaf axils. Petioles purple except on very young leaves; grooved above and pubescent with stiff hairs on the edges. Leaves widest at base and cordate to uneven; tapering evenly to an acute tip. Margins serrate to slightly doubly serrate. Venation pinnately branched and arching inwards at leaf margins; appear to be about 14 lateral veins per leaf. Leaves sparsely pubescent both above and below; underside is paler but not glaucous. No flower or fruit structures present at time of observation.
